From 79d6c98bc9bdaa4a0a6257361692cbe8428b8f36 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw CI <ci@rivonclaw.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 07:14:53 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): stream Feishu card deltas

Why:
- Keep Feishu CardKit replies on the channel dispatcher so group-chat defaults do not create a second message through the message tool.
- Show a transient Thinking placeholder before the first model token, then replace it and stream on the same card.
- Preserve append-safe partial and block deltas without replaying overlapping text.
- Surface rejected CardKit updates and close the same card with exact final content.

Upstream:
- Backport openclaw/openclaw#82419 (f436b4310a) and openclaw/openclaw#90181 (1f1ce8a1fe), with Feishu dispatcher routing and placeholder lifecycle for CardKit streaming.

Removal:
- Drop when the pinned OpenClaw version includes both upstream fixes and explicitly keeps Feishu CardKit replies on automatic source delivery with a same-card waiting state.

Tests:
- apps/desktop/src/channels/vendor-feishu-card-streaming.sentinel.test.ts
- extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts
- extensions/feishu/src/streaming-card.test.ts
